==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glissade
<hw>Glis`sade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>glisser</ets> to slip.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sliding, as down a
snow slope.</def> <rj><au>Tyndall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dance step consisting of a glide or slide to one
side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glissando</ent>⟦br⟧
